    <body>
        <div xml:id="NA392-kiḷavi">
            <p type="edition">1. iḵtu iravukkuṟi mukampukkatu. 2. varaivu nīṭu āṟṟāḷāya talaimakaḷait tōḻi varaivuṇartti vaṟpuṟuttiyatūumām (ET: vaṟpuṟīiyatūumām).</p>
            <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is how the confidante encouraged HER who was unable to bear it when being informed of the separation. 2. It is also how the marriage was announced.</p>
            </div>
      <div xml:id="NA392">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            kaṭuñcuṟā veṟinta koṭuntāṭ ṭantai</l>
<l>            puḷḷimiḻ peruṅkaṭaṟ koḷḷāṉ ceṉṟeṉa</l>
<l>            maṉaiyaḻu toḻinta puṉṟalaic ciṟāar</l>
<l>            tuṉaiyatiṉ muyaṉṟa tīṅka ṇuṅkiṉ</l>
<l>            paṇaikoṇ vemmulaip pāṭupeṟ ṟuvakkum</l>
<l>            peṇṇai vēli yuḻaikaṭ cīṟūr</l>
<l>            naṉmaṉai yaṟiyi ṉaṉṟumaṟ ṟilla</l>
<l>            cemma ṉeñcamoṭu tāmvantu peyarnta</l>
<l>            kāṉalō ṭaḻiyunar pōlām pāṉāṇ</l>
<l>            muṉipaṭar kaḷaiyiṉuṅ kaḷaipa</l>
<l>            naṉipē raṉpiṉar kāta lōrē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l >If he knew [our] good house</l>
<l rend="indent">	in the small village in the vicinity of the palmyra fence,</l>
<l rend="indent2">	where the ruddy-headed kids left behind crying in the house,</l>
<l rend="indent3">	since [their] bent-legged<note place="foot">T.V.G. prefers to read <term xml:lang="ta">koṭun tāḷ</term> here in a different way (deviating from the formulaic sense), namely as "cruel task".</note> father who threw the fierce shark</l>
<l rend="indent4">	went without taking [them] to the big sea buzzing with birds,</l>
<l rend="indent2">	rejoice in getting, singing with hot breasts,</l>
<l rend="indent2">	with [the help of] a bamboo [stick]</l>
<l rend="indent">	the palmyra fruit with sweet toddy</l>
<l rend="indent">	for which they made an unhasty effort(?),</l>
<l rend="indent4">	it would be<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">tilla</term> as particle of wish probably expresses here that it is not the case (that HE knows), while <term xml:lang="ta">maṟṟu</term> is exclusive: if he knew just that.</note> good,</l>
<l>– [our] lover who has very great love.</l>
<l>	Even if hateful affliction destroyed [him]<note place="foot">Since <term xml:lang="ta">aḻiyunar</term> can only refer to the man, how else to make sense of <term xml:lang="ta">kaḷaiyiṉum</term> here, although the usual topos is that HE removes HER affliction?</note> at midnight,</l>
<l rend="indent">when he seemed to be desolate along with the seashore grove</l>
<l rend="inden2t">from where he returned after having come with an exalted heart,</l>
<l rend="indent3">he will remove [it].</l>
      </lg>
      </div>
